{"questionId":"5275561","questionHtml":"<p>Two isolated point masses, P of mass <em>m</em> and Q of mass 2<em>m</em>, are separated by a distance 3<em>d</em>. X is a point a distance <em>d</em> from P and 2<em>d</em> from Q.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/ff71053d48d73bece97bdb20b7f7b55d1cac567d.png\"></p>\n<p>What is the net gravitational field strength at X and the net gravitational potential at X?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width:346px;height:179px;border-color:#000000;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:29px;\">\n<td style=\"width:45px;height:29px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width:142.083px;height:29px;text-align:center;\">\n<strong>Net gravitational field </strong><strong>strength at X</strong>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width:128.917px;height:29px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Net gravitational<br>potential at X</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px;\">\n<td style=\"width:45px;height:29px;\">A.</td>\n<td style=\"width:142.083px;height:29px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:128.917px;height:29px;text-align:center;\">0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:45px;\">B.</td>\n<td style=\"width:142.083px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:128.917px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mi>d</mi></mfrac></math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px;\">\n<td style=\"width:45px;height:29px;\">C.</td>\n<td style=\"width:142.083px;height:29px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:128.917px;height:29px;text-align:center;\">0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px;\">\n<td style=\"width:45px;height:29px;\">D.</td>\n<td style=\"width:142.083px;height:29px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:128.917px;height:29px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>G</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mi>d</mi></mfrac></math></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"5275561","referenceCode":"23M.1.HL.TZ1.30","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Two isolated point masses, P of mass m and Q of mass 2m, are separated by a distance 3d. X is a point a distance d from P and 2d from Q. What is the net gravitational field strengt","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"30","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 10: Fields","10.1 – Describing fields","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 10: Fields"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}